<title>USA: Activision ships MechWarrior 2: Mercenaries.</title>
<headline>Activision ships MechWarrior 2: Mercenaries.</headline>
<dateline>LOS ANGELES 1996-10-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Activision Inc said Wednesday it has shipped its video game MechWarrior 2: Mercenaries, a sequel to the popular MechWarrior 2, to over 10,000 stores in the the United States and Canada.</p>
<p>The 3-D battle simulation game follows last year's release of MechWarrior 2, which has shipped more than 700,000 retail units worldwide to date, the company said.</p>
<p>MechWarrior 2: Mercenaries features proprietary Internet drivers which permit up to eight players to compete simultaneously over the Internet.  Gamers can also compete over a local area network (LAN) or one-on-one via modem.</p>
